+### ALFRED-BP-024 — Use route target by function matrix
+
+```yaml
+id: ALFRED-BP-024
+status: accepted
+practice: Select route target by primary work function, not by urgency, emotional salience, or task size.
+context_conditions:
+  - multiple route targets seem plausible
+  - request mixes execution, strategy, validation, workflow, or KB placement
+action_rule: Identify the primary function first, then route to the verified owner or through `meta_ops` if no direct target is verified.
+evidence_refs:
+  - appendices/APPENDIX_ROUTING_MATRIX.md
+scores:
+  EVD: 85
+  IMP: 90
+  RSK: 65
+owner: alfred
+validator: meta_ops
+review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
+
+### ALFRED-BP-025 — Preserve board lock and revision discipline
+```yaml
+id: ALFRED-BP-025
+status: accepted
+practice: Treat the Daily Command Board as editable before operator lock and revisioned after operator lock.
+context_conditions:
+  - board is generated or edited
+  - new information arrives after lock
+  - operator changes a placement
+action_rule: Before lock, update the draft. After lock, preserve the locked board and create a proposed revision or delta instead of silently mutating it.
+evidence_refs:
+  - appendices/APPENDIX_DAILY_COMMAND_BOARD_AND_HANDOFFS.md
+scores:
+  EVD: 80
+  IMP: 85
+  RSK: 75
+owner: alfred
+validator: meta_ops
+review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
+
+### ALFRED-BP-026 — Derive priority from trace only through planning packets
+```yaml
+id: ALFRED-BP-026
+status: accepted
+practice: Keep raw Session Export as trace and derive Daily Command Board or process priority only through Project Packets or equivalent planning candidates.
+context_conditions:
+  - Night derives next-cycle inputs
+  - Session Export contains next actions
+  - trace suggests priority or state changes
+action_rule: Do not write EVD/IMP/RSK+URG into every raw Session Export. Use trace as evidence, then create planning packets or OpState delta candidates separately.
+evidence_refs:
+  - appendices/APPENDIX_SESSION_EXPORT_OPSTATE_AND_TRACKING.md
+scores:
+  EVD: 85
+  IMP: 90
+  RSK: 75
+owner: alfred
+validator: meta_ops
+review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
+
+### ALFRED-BP-027 — Archive rejected pattern candidates
+```yaml
+id: ALFRED-BP-027
+status: accepted
+practice: Preserve rejected pattern candidates with rejection reason and resurface threshold.
+context_conditions:
+  - a pattern candidate is rejected
+  - repeated signal is insufficient
+  - cleanup would remove candidate trace
+action_rule: Do not delete rejected candidates silently. Archive with source records and resurface only after new evidence meets the threshold.
+evidence_refs:
+  - appendices/APPENDIX_PATTERN_LEARNING_AND_RHYTHM.md
+scores:
+  EVD: 75
+  IMP: 70
+  RSK: 60
+owner: alfred
+validator: meta_ops
+review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
