+### ALFRED-BP-028 — Keep cleanup artifacts out of doctrine
+```yaml
+id: ALFRED-BP-028
+status: accepted
+practice: Treat cleanup prompt flows, patch proposals, and handover folders as process-control evidence, not as accepted Alfred doctrine.
+context_conditions:
+  - cleanup artifacts are stored under appendices
+  - proposal diffs contain operational language
+  - executor handovers are reviewed later
+action_rule: Use cleanup artifacts only to guide controlled edits. Do not promote their wording into canonical doctrine unless distilled into the correct owner with source basis and validation.
+evidence_refs:
+  - appendices/APPENDIX_ALFRED_KB_CLEANUP_PROMPT_FLOW.md
+  - appendices/cleanup_patch_proposals/
+scores:
+  EVD: 80
+  IMP: 80
+  RSK: 70
+owner: alfred
+validator: meta_ops
+review_due: 2026-07-25
+```
